definition:
to show emotion (such as mirth, joy, or scorn) with a chuckle or explosive vocal sound                                      
             
             The audience was laughing hysterically.

to find amusement or pleasure in something                                      
             
             laughed at his own clumsiness

to become amused or derisive                                      
             
             a very skeptical public laughed at our early efforts

to produce the sound or appearance of laughter                                      
             
             a laughing brook

to be of a kind that inspires joy                                      
             
             the blue sky of Autumn laughs above

to influence or move by laughter                                      
             
             laughed the bad singer off the stage

to utter with a laugh                                      
             
             laughs her consent
the act of laughing
a cause for derision or merriment : joke
an expression of scorn or mockery : jeer

diversion, sport                                      
             
             play baseball just for laughs
to show that you are happy or that you think something is funny by smiling and making a sound from your throat
to think or say that someone or something is foolish and does not deserve serious attention or respect
to not be bothered by something
the act or sound of laughing
something that causes laughter : something funny or foolish
a funny person
to show amusement, joy, or scorn by smiling and making sounds (as chuckling) in the throat
in: The audience was laughing hysterically.

a very skeptical public laughed at our early efforts
a laughing brook

laughs her consent

definition: to make the noise with your voice that shows you think something is funny
to show that you think someone or something is stupid or deserves no respect
to laugh very loudly and coarsely
in: We talked and laughed late into the night.
laugh at: The audience didn’t laugh at his jokes.
laugh about: They were still laughing about the experience years later.
burst out laughing  (=start laughing suddenly): She burst out laughing when she saw what he was wearing.
When I told them my idea, they just laughed.
laugh in someone’s face: If someone had told me this was going to happen, I would’ve laughed in their face.
be laughing
don’t make me laugh
laugh all the way to the bank
laugh someone/something out of court
laugh up your sleeve
no laughing matter
not know whether to laugh or cry
you have to laugh
you’ll be laughing on the other side of your face

definition: to smile while making sounds with your voice that show you think something is funny or you are happy:
the act or sound of laughing:
an enjoyable or funny activity:
someone who is funny:
to make the sounds and movements of the face and body that express happiness or amusement, or that sometimes express ridicule or anxiety:
Sometimes when you laugh at someone, you are ridiculing that person:
the sounds and movements of the face and body that express happiness or amusement, or that sometimes express ridicule or anxiety:
infml A laugh is also an amusing or ridiculous situation or person:
